  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR / ACCOUNTING MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a reliable HR / Accounting Manager to handle both human resources and basic accounting functions. This role supports staff management, payroll, and company financial records to ensure smooth daily operations.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><p><strong>Human Resources</strong></p><ul><li><p>Manage recruitment, onboarding, and employee records</p></li><li><p>Handle payroll, leave, attendance, and benefits</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with employment laws and company policies</p></li><li><p>Support staff performance reviews and disciplinary matters</p></li><li><p>Handle HR-related queries professionally and confidentially</p></li></ul><p><strong>Accounting</strong></p><ul><li><p>Manage daily accounting entries and financial records</p></li><li><p>Prepare invoices, payments, and expense claims</p></li><li><p>Handle monthly payroll processing and CPF/statutory submissions</p></li><li><p>Assist in monthly financial reports and audits</p></li><li><p>Liaise with auditors, banks, and external accountants</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in HR, Accounting, Finance, or related field</p></li><li><p>2–5 years of relevant HR and accounting experience</p></li><li><p>Basic knowledge of payroll, employment regulations, and bookkeeping</p></li><li><p>Familiar with accounting or HR software</p></li><li><p>Organized, detail-oriented, and able to work independently</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Preferred Skills</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Strong communication and interpersonal skills</p></li><li><p>Confidential and trustworthy</p></li><li><p>Ability to multitask and meet deadlines</p></li></ul>",
